github is a centralized repository where developers push the code

it will track the changes

who did the commit

when did the commit happen

to clone repository use the below command
------------------------------------------------------

git clone repository url

after cloning the repository how to go inside the repository

cd repositoryname

after going inside the repository you can make changes are create new files or delete existing files

after making the changes you have to push to the remote repository

commands used to push to github
--------------------------------------------
git add .
git commit -m "some message"
git push